THE FOUNDATION IS ORGANIZED TO PERFORM CHARITABLE AND EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES WITHIN THE MEANING OF INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3) AND TEXAS TAX CODE SECTION 11.1B(C)(1). SPECIFICALLY, THE FOUNDATION IS ORGANIZED TO PROVIDE RESOURCES FOR YOUTH, EDUCATION AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT.

THE NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES REPORTED IN PART V, LINE 2A IS NONE. THE SALARY REFLECTED ON FORM 990, PART IX, LINE 5 IS ALLOCATED TO THE FOUNDATION BY ROUND ROCK BASEBALL CLUB, LP AND IT IS REPORTED ON THE FORM W-3, TRANSMITTAL OF WAGE AND TAX STATEMENTS, OF ROUND ROCK BASEBALL CLUB, LP. THE FOUNDATION REIMBURSED ROUND ROCK BASEBALL, LP FOR THE SALARY, AND ALL OTHER EXPENSES INCURRED ON BEHALF OF THE FOUNDATION.
